CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 10, 1959, pg. A2 reads: "Thanks Church - The Rev. Charles H. Foggie, local NAACP branch president, gratefully receives a $50 check from Mrs. Annabelle Jefferson. The check represents a down payment on a life membership for the Lincoln Avenue Church of God, the Rev. C. M. Morgan, pastor.  Board member, Mrs. Coretta Ogburn, looks on. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Rev. Charles Foggie receiving check from Annabelle Jefferson, with Coretta Ogburn looking on, in Ebenezer Baptist Church during NAACP membership meeting
